00:01:46.583 --> 00:01:48.583
'How many stars sparkle in the sky?'

00:01:49.375 --> 00:01:51.708
'Ever tried counting them?'

00:01:52.333 --> 00:01:58.875
'It would take 6,000 years to
count those in our galaxy.'

00:02:00.416 --> 00:02:02.583
'And how many such galaxies exist?'

00:02:02.833 --> 00:02:06.625
'Scientists reckon, two billion more.'

00:02:07.000 --> 00:02:12.291
'Isn't it possible that amongst
these billions of celestial bodies'

00:02:12.625 --> 00:02:16.000
'a planet with people like us, exists?'

00:02:16.416 --> 00:02:20.166
'As we explore the space looking for them,'

00:02:20.458 --> 00:02:24.708
'could they be coming here,
looking for us?'

00:06:14.083 --> 00:06:18.500
'What the thief stole was the
gadget to recall his spaceship.'

00:06:18.708 --> 00:06:22.333
'Without this remote
he could not return home.'

00:06:22.625 --> 00:06:27.041
'He neither knew our language,
nor did he have a friend here.'

00:06:27.333 --> 00:06:31.291
'Alone, anguished,
his only thought was...'

00:06:31.583 --> 00:06:33.416
"how will I return home?"

00:06:56.291 --> 00:07:01.708
