00:34:59.458 --> 00:35:02.166
We read minds.
There's no confusion.

00:35:02.333 --> 00:35:05.250
Here, you utter something
and mean something else.

00:35:05.333 --> 00:35:07.750
A two-letter word can have
four different meanings.

00:35:08.125 --> 00:35:12.916
When you nod and say "oh,"
it means "Oh, that's cool."

00:35:14.208 --> 00:35:17.500
When your eyes pop out,
"oh!" means bad news.

00:35:17.791 --> 00:35:19.625
"Your mother-in-law is moving in."
"Oh!"

00:35:19.916 --> 00:35:21.166
Shock.

00:35:21.625 --> 00:35:24.125
When angry, you thunder.

00:35:24.500 --> 00:35:27.833
"Oh! You'll pay for that blunder!"

00:35:28.250 --> 00:35:31.125
And when your thought is deep,
your "oh" is long!

00:35:31.916 --> 00:35:34.666
"Oh! I see!"

00:35:35.208 --> 00:35:38.458
As you hear the words,
you've got to watch the expression

00:35:38.583 --> 00:35:40.541
to get the real meaning.

00:35:40.666 --> 00:35:44.875
It's torture!
It took me six hours to learn Hindi.

00:35:45.166 --> 00:35:48.083
A whole language in six hours?

00:35:48.166 --> 00:35:50.708
No one let me hold hands.

00:35:51.208 --> 00:35:53.416
Finally, a nice lady lent her hand.

00:35:53.500 --> 00:35:57.416
I held it and transferred
her language into my system.

00:35:57.500 --> 00:36:02.333
Man, there's no limit
