You're talking!

00:49:32.916 --> 00:49:35.750
Bro, I need your help.

00:49:35.833 --> 00:49:37.958
Pepper cleared up your throat!

00:49:38.041 --> 00:49:39.708
Bro, come with me.

00:49:39.791 --> 00:49:42.750
Memory and making out
have a direct connection!

00:49:43.458 --> 00:49:47.833
We should update the doctors.
"Get laid, get well!"

00:49:47.958 --> 00:49:50.375
It's urgent, bro!

00:49:50.500 --> 00:49:51.875
Okay, let's go.

00:49:58.708 --> 00:50:00.291
Stop! Stop!

00:50:00.375 --> 00:50:01.541
Stop, bro!

00:50:05.708 --> 00:50:09.583
The jerk robbed me right here.

00:50:10.083 --> 00:50:12.791
I need my chain, bro.
I must get it back.

00:50:13.041 --> 00:50:15.083
Is it precious?
- It's priceless!

00:50:15.458 --> 00:50:18.208
The thief must be a local.

00:50:18.541 --> 00:50:21.333
But he must have sold the loot in Delhi.

00:50:21.416 --> 00:50:25.083
If he sells pricey stuff here,
he'd get caught.

00:50:26.041 --> 00:50:27.958
Then I must go.

00:50:28.375 --> 00:50:30.041
Where?

00:50:30.583 --> 00:50:31.750
Delhi.

00:50:55.791 --> 00:50:57.375
Officer!
- Yeah?

00:50:57.833 --> 00:51:00.916
Somebody stole my remote control.
- Are you tipsy?

00:51:01.208 --> 00:51:04.208
You're expecting the police force
to track your TV remote?

00:51:04.666 --> 00:51:07.583
It's not a TV remote!
- Then?

00:51:08.458 --> 00:51:11.750
Can't tell you.
But it's like a chain.

00:51:11.833 --> 00:51:13.416
Really precious.

00:51:13.583 --> 00:51:15.458
Where was it stolen?
- In Mandawa.

00:51:17.250 --> 00:51:18.875
The theft took place at Mandawa

00:51:18.958 --> 00:51:21.250
and you're searching for
it in Delhi, you idiot?

00:51:21.708 --> 00:51:23.541
The thief came to Delhi.

00:51:23.625 --> 00:51:25.625
So?
- So where's the thief?

00:51:25.708 --> 00:51:28.666
Blockhead!
It's a city of 15 million.

00:51:28.833 --> 00:51:30.416
Police are humans, not God.

00:51:30.500 --> 00:51:33.541
'Police are humans, not God.'

00:51:35.291 --> 00:51:37.250
Only God can help you.

00:51:37.333 --> 00:51:39.708
'Only God can help you.'

00:51:39.958 --> 00:51:42.916
Surrender to God, you'll succeed.

00:51:43.000 --> 00:51:45.583
'Surrender to God.'

00:51:45.750 --> 00:51:48.000
Only God knows.

00:51:48.083 --> 00:51:50.166
'Only God knows.'

00:51:50.416 --> 00:51:52.250
Ask God, not me!

00:51:52.333 --> 00:51:54.750
'Ask God!'

00:51:55.000 --> 00:51:57.083
Trust in God, my child.

00:51:57.166 --> 00:51:58.666
'Trust in God, my child.'

00:51:58.750 --> 00:52:04.208
'Who was this God?
Everyone said only He could help.'

00:52:04.833 --> 00:52:08.083
'What I saw blew my mind.'

00:52:08.166 --> 00:52:11.958
'Earthlings had figured out
who had manufactured them!'

00:52:12.416 --> 00:52:16.666
'Their creator lived with them.
He had millions of houses.'

00:52:17.000 --> 00:52:23.375
'Earthlings took their problems to Him,
which He solved for a small fee.'

00:52:23.833 --> 00:52:27.458
'My planet had no such facility.'

00:52:27.791 --> 00:52:31.583
'I could not believe it!
So I decided to test it.'

00:52:34.625 --> 00:52:36.666
One take-away God.

00:52:36.750 --> 00:52:40.166
Which one?
One for 20, 50, 100 or 500?

00:52:40.666 --> 00:52:44.041
What's the difference between the
one for 20 and the one for 500?

00:52:44.125 --> 00:52:46.375
Just the size.
Otherwise ditto.

00:52:46.458 --> 00:52:49.958
The one for 20 is equally
efficient, right?

00:52:50.958 --> 00:52:54.458
Okay, give me 15.
Nothing less.

00:53:07.416 --> 00:53:11.291
God, I am famished.
Get me some food please.

00:53:23.708 --> 00:53:25.333
'I went bananas!'

00:53:25.750 --> 00:53:29.750
'God actually worked!
Now I could go home.'

00:53:29.833 --> 00:53:32.833
God, my remote is stolen.

00:53:33.125 --> 00:53:35.458
Please find it.
I want to go home.

00:53:49.500 --> 00:53:53.708
God's battery died.
Worked once, then kaput.

00:53:54.416 --> 00:53:56.541
What do you mean?
- Stick a new battery in.

00:53:56.666 --> 00:53:57.791
Where does it go?

00:53:57.875 --> 00:54:01.000
It needs no battery.
- Then why is it off?

00:54:01.375 --> 00:54:05.000
Manufacturing defect?
- I make no defective stuff.

00:54:06.083 --> 00:54:10.833
You made this God?
- Of course! With my own hands.

00:54:11.458 --> 00:54:14.250
Did you make God or did God make you?

00:54:14.375 --> 00:54:19.625
He made us all.
I only make His statues.

00:54:20.000 --> 00:54:21.916
Why the statues?

00:54:22.000 --> 00:54:25.666
To worship Him.
To voice our problems.

00:54:26.166 --> 00:54:30.375
Is there a transmitter inside?
How can He hear us?

00:54:31.416 --> 00:54:36.041
God needs no transmitter.
He hears directly.

00:54:36.208 --> 00:54:39.125
Directly?
Then why the statue?

00:54:39.500 --> 00:54:41.750
What's with him?

00:54:42.958 --> 00:54:47.000
Do you want to bust my business?
What's your problem?

00:54:47.500 --> 00:54:49.416
My remote is stolen, Sir.

00:54:49.666 --> 00:54:53.000
I'm requesting God to find it.
But He doesn't reply.

00:54:53.458 --> 00:54:55.458
Are you tipsy?
- Meaning?

00:54:55.541 --> 00:54:58.708
You're overloading this pint-sized God.

00:54:58.875 --> 00:55:01.500
His itty-bitty feet
can't chase the thief.

00:55:01.583 --> 00:55:04.666
Brother, the big God is inside the temple.

00:55:05.125 --> 00:55:07.458
He'll run fast.

00:55:07.541 --> 00:55:11.250
Offer Him coconut and some money.
He'll deliver.

00:55:11.416 --> 00:55:13.291
That'll be 200.

00:55:18.666 --> 00:55:22.916
'Earthlings waited with fees
to get their work done.'

00:55:23.333 --> 00:55:26.041
'Two hours later,
I got the appointment.'

00:55:26.291 --> 00:55:27.666
God!

00:55:29.333 --> 00:55:31.916
God, please get my remote back.

00:55:34.708 --> 00:55:36.958
Where is it?
- Move!

00:55:37.041 --> 00:55:38.916
Wait, He didn't deliver my stuff.

00:55:39.250 --> 00:55:43.541
He didn't deliver!
I paid the fee.

00:55:43.625 --> 00:55:45.666
Your work will be done.
- But when?

00:55:45.750 --> 00:55:48.208
Can't say when, but it will be done.

00:55:48.291 --> 00:55:51.125
Move!
- But when will I get it?

00:55:51.208 --> 00:55:52.708
Don't block the line, scram!

00:55:52.791 --> 00:55:55.583
If I scram, He might
give it to someone else.

00:55:55.708 --> 00:55:58.458
Are you tipsy?
- Lady, please!

00:55:58.875 --> 00:56:00.500
Where will I get my stuff?

00:56:00.583 --> 00:56:02.416
At the mental hospital!

00:56:02.500 --> 00:56:06.416
What? I paid here and the
delivery at the mental hospital?

00:56:06.500 --> 00:56:08.833
Throw him out!
- At least give me a receipt.

00:56:09.708 --> 00:56:13.083
How will I claim my delivery
without a receipt?

00:56:13.166 --> 00:56:15.416
Get out!

00:56:15.541 --> 00:56:18.250
But what about my remote?
- Leave!

00:56:25.958 --> 00:56:28.875
I can't find my shoes.

00:56:29.208 --> 00:56:32.375
Somebody might've taken them.
Now you take your pick.

00:56:32.791 --> 00:56:35.041
Rotation is a routine at temples.

00:56:49.083 --> 00:56:52.875
He took the payment,
but didn't deliver.

00:56:57.500 --> 00:56:58.833
What's his name?

00:56:58.958 --> 00:57:01.125
They call Him God.
- Real name?

00:57:01.375 --> 00:57:02.916
No idea.

00:57:04.583 --> 00:57:05.833
Where does he live?

00:57:06.375 --> 00:57:08.500
In that temple.

00:57:08.750 --> 00:57:12.500
You handed him the cash?
- No. I put it in His box.

00:57:12.583 --> 00:57:15.166
Did he say he'd do the job?
- He says nothing.

00:57:15.291 --> 00:57:16.958
Is he mute?

00:57:17.041 --> 00:57:18.833
Perhaps...
Maybe.

00:57:19.250 --> 00:57:21.000
Oh.

00:57:22.500 --> 00:57:23.791
Describe him.

00:57:27.291 --> 00:57:28.750
Ditto.

00:57:31.166 --> 00:57:33.625
But bigger.

00:57:34.583 --> 00:57:35.916
Come closer.

00:57:37.791 --> 00:57:39.208
Are you tipsy?

00:57:40.333 --> 00:57:42.750
Yes. But how do you all know?

00:57:42.833 --> 00:57:46.375
Do you think I'm a jackass?
I've been a cop for 20 years.

00:57:46.541 --> 00:57:49.666
I can tell in a snap
who's tipsy and who's not.

00:57:50.625 --> 00:57:53.583
Kirpal, frisk him.

00:57:55.166 --> 00:57:57.625
Let me have a look.
- Sir.

00:57:58.958 --> 00:58:00.958
Dr. D'Mello.

00:58:01.500 --> 00:58:06.375
Doc, why get so buzzed
that you forget your faith?

00:58:06.541 --> 00:58:10.375
Mistook temple for a church!
Wanna rouse a riot?

00:58:11.000 --> 00:58:15.500
Go to church.
To your own God.

00:58:17.458 --> 00:58:18.500
Church?

00:59:07.708 --> 00:59:09.250
Get out of here!

00:59:09.333 --> 00:59:12.458
My stuff! My remote!
- Get out!

00:59:12.541 --> 00:59:15.833
God was crucified for your sins.
Ungrateful man!

00:59:16.125 --> 00:59:20.291
Crucified! When?

00:59:20.541 --> 00:59:22.208
2,000 years ago.

00:59:22.708 --> 00:59:24.291
For your sins.

00:59:24.416 --> 00:59:27.708
What did I do?
I just got here.

00:59:29.250 --> 00:59:31.333
Are you tipsy?
- Yes!

00:59:31.458 --> 00:59:34.375
God is watching you.
He's watching your behavior.

00:59:34.916 --> 00:59:36.458
Where?

00:59:36.750 --> 00:59:38.125
Where is God?

00:59:38.833 --> 00:59:40.125
What's in that mug?

00:59:40.208 --> 00:59:41.291
Wine.

00:59:41.875 --> 00:59:45.750
'Wine!
Now I got it!'

00:59:46.500 --> 00:59:49.291
'God was bored of coconut water.'

00:59:49.500 --> 00:59:53.333
'Now He preferred wine.
But wine was expensive.'

00:59:53.416 --> 00:59:55.541
'So I had to muster money.'

00:59:57.125 --> 01:00:01.875
'I got some from the dancing car.
And some from a gentleman'

01:00:01.958 --> 01:00:04.875
'who held out a bowl of dole everyday.'

01:00:05.125 --> 01:00:07.458
'You could withdraw as per your need.'

01:00:28.583 --> 01:00:30.666
Sir, is there a God's house nearby?

01:00:30.750 --> 01:00:32.166
Right there.

01:00:32.916 --> 01:00:37.708
"Preacher, let me drink"

01:00:38.625 --> 01:00:42.375
"in God's abode..."

01:00:45.666 --> 01:00:52.958
"Or show me a place
where there is no God...'

01:00:53.208 --> 01:00:56.041
Stop!
What's that?

01:00:56.125 --> 01:00:58.041
Wine, for God.

01:00:58.458 --> 01:00:59.583
Where is He?

01:01:40.458 --> 01:01:42.708
'This lady looked very sad.'

01:01:43.041 --> 01:01:45.791
'To know why,
I grabbed her hand.'

01:01:46.166 --> 01:01:48.625
Hitting on a widow, you lech!

01:01:49.875 --> 01:01:50.916
Widow?
How do you know?

01:01:51.000 --> 01:01:53.250
Don't you see she's clad in white?

01:02:05.208 --> 01:02:07.708
Is everything fine?
- Everything is fine.

01:02:12.708 --> 01:02:15.208
I am so sorry your husband's dead.

01:02:15.291 --> 01:02:16.833
What?
- When?

01:02:17.000 --> 01:02:20.041
How do I know?
You are clad in white.

01:02:20.375 --> 01:02:22.041
Brides wear white!

01:02:22.125 --> 01:02:24.708
No, widows wear white.

01:02:25.083 --> 01:02:27.166
Widows wear black, stupid!
- Got it?

01:02:39.750 --> 01:02:42.166
Are your husbands no more?
- Oh, God!

01:02:42.541 --> 01:02:44.791
I'm alive, you moron!
I'll whack you!

01:02:46.416 --> 01:02:50.166
'After many whacks, I learnt
that there wasn't one God.'

01:02:50.500 --> 01:02:52.166
'There were many Gods.'

01:02:52.250 --> 01:02:54.666
'Each with His own set of rules.'

01:02:55.041 --> 01:02:57.375
'Each God had come up
with His own company.'

01:02:57.958 --> 01:02:59.958
'They called it religion.'

01:03:00.375 --> 01:03:03.458
'Each company had its agents.'

01:03:03.750 --> 01:03:08.791
'All Earthlings belonged to some religion'

01:03:09.125 --> 01:03:13.750
'and followed the God
of that religion alone.'

01:03:14.333 --> 01:03:17.958
'What was my religion?
Who was my God?'

01:03:18.583 --> 01:03:21.416
'To find the remote
I had to know my God.'

01:03:37.083 --> 01:03:39.083
What are you doing?

01:03:39.291 --> 01:03:40.916
Where is the label?

01:03:41.125 --> 01:03:43.000
What label?

01:03:43.500 --> 01:03:45.166
The religion label.

01:03:46.000 --> 01:03:48.625
How do you know which
company he belongs to?

01:03:49.208 --> 01:03:50.708
Where does God label them?

01:04:00.833 --> 01:04:03.500
'Finding my religion was tough.'

01:04:04.041 --> 01:04:08.833
'So I decided to worship all Gods.'

01:04:09.166 --> 01:04:12.875
'Perhaps, one of them would
be my God, who'd help me.'

01:04:12.958 --> 01:04:19.458
"It's You Who governs
the world I hear."

01:04:19.708 --> 01:04:25.708
"Do listen to my plea.
My home beckons me."

01:04:25.958 --> 01:04:31.291
"God where are You?"

01:04:32.750 --> 01:04:38.750
"Tell me, where are You?"

01:04:39.875 --> 01:04:46.500
"To sanity You guide back
those who've lost their way..."

01:04:46.583 --> 01:04:52.666
"I too am completely lost.
Guide me too, I pray."

01:04:52.833 --> 01:04:57.916
"God where are You?"

01:04:59.625 --> 01:05:05.583
"Tell me, where are You?"

01:05:33.125 --> 01:05:36.458
"Shall I worship You in temples?"

01:05:36.541 --> 01:05:39.875
"In mosques do my faith I show?"

01:05:40.000 --> 01:05:46.583
"Or to a Gurudwara
would You like me to go?"

01:05:46.666 --> 01:05:53.208
"Temples and churches,
I looked everywhere."

01:05:53.375 --> 01:05:59.791
"My hope now,
has turned to despair."

01:06:00.083 --> 01:06:05.291
"My hope now,
has turned to despair."

01:06:06.875 --> 01:06:12.916
"My hope now,
has turned to despair."

01:06:17.125 --> 01:06:22.958
"Not a single ritual
did I ever flout..."

01:06:24.083 --> 01:06:29.916
"Like millions around
I submit without a doubt"

01:06:30.375 --> 01:06:35.333
"God where are You?"

01:06:37.000 --> 01:06:42.125
"Tell me, where are You?"

01:07:10.583 --> 01:07:17.000
"You have many names
And many faces too"

01:07:17.375 --> 01:07:23.458
"I've walked each of the myriad
paths which lead to You."

01:07:24.083 --> 01:07:30.666
"In no shrine did I find You."

01:07:30.750 --> 01:07:36.333
"What else should I do to find you?
Give a clue..."

01:07:37.500 --> 01:07:43.208
"What else should I do to find you?
Give a clue..."

01:07:44.375 --> 01:07:49.750
"What else should I do to find you?
Give a clue..."

01:07:54.666 --> 01:08:00.583
"I blindly follow and
with reverence treasure"

01:08:01.541 --> 01:08:07.333
"Your every whim and fancy
in more than ample measure."

01:08:07.833 --> 01:08:12.416
"God, where are You?"

01:08:14.500 --> 01:08:18.958
"Tell me, where are You?"

01:08:21.166 --> 01:08:26.416
"God, where are You?"

01:08:27.916 --> 01:08:34.208
"Tell me, where are You?"

01:08:43.416 --> 01:08:45.291
God, I'm all confused.

01:08:48.250 --> 01:08:53.000
What's my fault?
Why can't my voice reach you?

01:08:54.583 --> 01:08:57.166
Understand my plight.

01:08:57.583 --> 01:08:58.958
Give me some guidance.

01:09:00.166 --> 01:09:01.208
Please.

01:09:04.541 --> 01:09:06.625
Shall I talk to you with my hands clasped,

01:09:07.291 --> 01:09:11.625
or on bent knees,
head to the ground?

01:09:14.666 --> 01:09:16.375
Do I wake you with temple bells?

01:09:17.208 --> 01:09:19.166
Or call out on a loudspeaker?

01:09:20.250 --> 01:09:25.583
The Geeta, the Quran,
or the Bible, what do I read?

01:09:26.125 --> 01:09:30.166
Your different managers
say different things.

01:09:30.750 --> 01:09:35.333
Some insist fasting on Monday,
others urge on Tuesday.

01:09:35.750 --> 01:09:40.625
Some forbid food after sunset,
some after sunrise.

01:09:41.416 --> 01:09:45.333
Some say, worship the cow.
Others say, slaughter her.

01:09:45.916 --> 01:09:51.458
Some send me barefoot to the temple.
Some, wearing shoes to the church.

01:09:51.916 --> 01:09:54.583
What is right and what is wrong?

01:09:55.000 --> 01:09:57.375
I am clueless.

01:09:59.000 --> 01:10:01.666
I'm at a breaking point.

01:10:04.000 --> 01:10:06.166
I want to go home.

01:10:06.958 --> 01:10:10.875
I'll do whatever you ask.
Just get me home.

01:10:11.333 --> 01:10:13.125
Please.

01:10:14.666 --> 01:10:16.333
Say something.

01:10:17.541 --> 01:10:19.625
At least one of you...

01:10:20.250 --> 01:10:22.083
give me an answer.

01:10:22.833 --> 01:10:23.875
Please.

01:10:26.250 --> 01:10:27.291
Please.

01:10:29.375 --> 01:10:31.291
Please.

01:10:40.625 --> 01:10:43.583
'Missing: God.'

01:10:52.166 --> 01:10:53.458
'Missing: God.'

01:11:39.041 --> 01:11:40.625
Why the lock, man?

01:11:40.750 --> 01:11:42.791
I won't let you go today!

01:11:43.250 --> 01:11:44.666
Open it!
It's my entry!

01:11:44.750 --> 01:11:48.624
Lord Shiva, the slayer of sins,
who fears none...

01:11:50.791 --> 01:11:53.749
Who are you?
- Don't you recognize me?

01:11:54.250 --> 01:11:56.083
I'm Tipsy!

01:11:57.833 --> 01:12:00.208
Where the hell is the security?

01:12:00.291 --> 01:12:03.375
Do I perform for drunkards in the toilet?

01:12:05.625 --> 01:12:07.875
Unlock the door!
Right now!

01:12:07.958 --> 01:12:09.625
First give me my remote!

01:12:09.708 --> 01:12:12.958
What remote?
- The remote of my spaceship.

01:12:13.416 --> 01:12:14.458
Spaceship?

01:12:14.624 --> 01:12:18.041
Did you forget?
For the zillionth time,

01:12:18.458 --> 01:12:21.291
I'm not from here.
I'm from a far off planet.

01:12:21.416 --> 01:12:22.583
Put this away!

01:12:22.875 --> 01:12:26.750
Give me my remote,
and I go home. Got it?

01:12:27.041 --> 01:12:30.458
Brother, let me go.
I've little kids at home.

01:12:30.541 --> 01:12:32.958
I know!
You fathered two Gods.

01:12:33.041 --> 01:12:35.624
Both are centuries old.
They can be home alone.

01:12:35.708 --> 01:12:38.541
First my remote,
then your family reunion.

01:12:39.375 --> 01:12:40.916
Oh, God, please save me!

01:12:41.000 --> 01:12:42.666
There's a God above you, too?

01:12:42.749 --> 01:12:44.125
Lord Shiva, help!

01:12:44.208 --> 01:12:45.250
Where is he?

01:12:47.958 --> 01:12:51.583
Now presenting the dance of Shiva,
the Fearless!

01:12:51.666 --> 01:12:52.791
Help!

01:12:56.333 --> 01:12:57.374
Help!

01:13:04.291 --> 01:13:06.291
Help!

01:13:08.041 --> 01:13:09.125
Help!

01:13:27.000 --> 01:13:29.541
Hail Lord Shiva...

01:13:48.125 --> 01:13:52.583
Hail Lord Shiva.
- Hail Lord Shiva!

01:13:52.666 --> 01:13:58.291
I was meditating on the
snowy peaks of the Himalayas...

01:13:58.666 --> 01:14:01.875
and suddenly, there was light!

01:14:02.000 --> 01:14:04.166
Dazzling light!

01:14:05.041 --> 01:14:10.500
It came from a bead
lying in the snow.

01:14:11.125 --> 01:14:15.125
'I shut my eyes and invoked God.'

01:14:15.708 --> 01:14:18.791
'Next moment,
I was connected.'

01:14:18.875 --> 01:14:21.875
I said, "God, enlighten me.

01:14:21.958 --> 01:14:24.166
What is this miraculous object,

01:14:24.250 --> 01:14:27.666
that is warm even in this biting cold?"

01:14:28.083 --> 01:14:29.416
God said,

01:14:29.500 --> 01:14:34.375
"It's a divine bead
from Lord Shiva's necklace.

01:14:34.458 --> 01:14:40.291
Take it and enshrine it
in a grand temple.

01:14:40.375 --> 01:14:46.583
Sighting this bead
will heal all suffering."

01:14:46.666 --> 01:14:49.875
Hail Lord Shiva.

01:14:50.500 --> 01:14:52.541
Are you ready for the sighting of...

01:14:53.250 --> 01:14:56.375
the divine bead from
Lord Shiva's necklace?

01:14:57.291 --> 01:14:59.833
Hail Lord Shiva!

01:14:59.958 --> 01:15:04.583
Hail Lord Shiva.

01:15:04.916 --> 01:15:09.416
Hail Lord Shiva!

01:15:18.041 --> 01:15:20.833
Hail Lord Shiva!

01:15:20.916 --> 01:15:22.916
Hail Lord Shiva!

01:15:23.000 --> 01:15:25.166
Stop.
- Let him through.

01:15:25.333 --> 01:15:28.208
He's awed by the sight.

01:15:28.291 --> 01:15:30.291
Come.
- Hail Lord Shiva.

01:15:30.375 --> 01:15:33.750
Not there, child.
Come here.

01:15:33.833 --> 01:15:35.750
Express your ecstasy.

01:15:35.833 --> 01:15:38.291
Hail Lord Shiva.

01:15:38.375 --> 01:15:41.875
Hail Lord Shiva.

01:15:42.208 --> 01:15:44.625
God, where are you?
Please step out,

01:15:44.708 --> 01:15:46.708
'I want to thank you.'

01:15:48.166 --> 01:15:49.708
He's right here.

01:15:50.166 --> 01:15:51.875
I met Him in the toilet.

01:15:51.958 --> 01:15:54.625
I asked for my property
and He bolted.

01:15:54.916 --> 01:15:56.750
I thought He vamoosed.

01:15:57.000 --> 01:16:00.583
But, no!
He led me to my property.

01:16:00.875 --> 01:16:03.333
Hail Lord Shiva.

01:16:04.291 --> 01:16:06.375
This isn't Lord Shiva's bead.

01:16:06.500 --> 01:16:09.416
It's my property,
misdelivered to you.

01:16:09.500 --> 01:16:11.500
Your bead must be
misdelivered too.

01:16:11.750 --> 01:16:13.166
Ask God, He is right here.

01:16:13.250 --> 01:16:16.583
God, do step forward, clarify.

01:16:18.583 --> 01:16:21.291
Anyway, I'll take my property.

01:16:23.500 --> 01:16:27.458
That's mine!
Why are you stopping me?

01:16:28.500 --> 01:16:33.541
Hail Lord Shiva.
- Hail Lord Shiva!

01:16:45.041 --> 01:16:49.500
"A traveler of dreams..."

01:16:50.291 --> 01:16:53.875
"Neither a devotee, nor an unbeliever..."

01:16:55.416 --> 01:16:59.833
"Oh Lord, tell me..."

01:17:00.708 --> 01:17:04.500
"Where am I?"

01:17:05.500 --> 01:17:10.333
"Why do you play this game
of hide and seek with me?"

01:17:10.833 --> 01:17:14.875
"Please take me home."

01:17:15.166 --> 01:17:20.166
"My heart is lost."

01:17:20.500 --> 01:17:25.208
"My heart is lost."

01:17:32.125 --> 01:17:37.708
Since when have you felt
that you're from another planet?

01:17:40.000 --> 01:17:46.125
Listen, you need to see a psychiatrist.

01:17:47.125 --> 01:17:50.083
Time up! That's all you
get for 500 rupees.

01:17:50.166 --> 01:17:51.208
Just a minute.

01:17:58.125 --> 01:18:00.125
Here's my card.

01:18:00.833 --> 01:18:04.916
My number's on it. If you wish,
I'll get you an appointment.

01:18:05.333 --> 01:18:07.833
Feel free to call. Okay?

01:18:09.083 --> 01:18:13.416
Okay.

01:18:12.916 --> 01:18:15.041
Thank you, Mr. Pandey.

01:18:16.666 --> 01:18:19.708
You think my story is a lie, don't you?

01:18:21.833 --> 01:18:26.041
Then go back to
the suicidal dog, Nikku!

01:18:26.625 --> 01:18:29.125
That's the story for you.

01:18:35.833 --> 01:18:39.500
Mr. Pandey,
I need to go back in for 2 minutes.

01:18:40.250 --> 01:18:43.458
Quit going in and out!

01:18:43.875 --> 01:18:48.625
Another 500 and he's all yours.

01:18:48.708 --> 01:18:52.500
When did I mention Nikku,
the suicidal dog?

01:18:52.875 --> 01:18:54.583
You didn't.

01:18:54.750 --> 01:18:56.791
So how do you know?

01:18:57.083 --> 01:19:02.000
When you held my hand,
I read your thoughts.

01:19:02.916 --> 01:19:04.708
You thought,
"This story is dead.

01:19:04.791 --> 01:19:06.416
I got to live with the Nikku story."

01:19:06.500 --> 01:19:09.500
Don't lie!
I must have mentioned it.

01:19:09.583 --> 01:19:13.083
I cannot lie.
Lying needs language.

01:19:13.166 --> 01:19:15.666
And on my planet, we hold
hands and read minds.

01:19:17.750 --> 01:19:19.000
Give me your hand.
- No way.

01:19:19.250 --> 01:19:21.666
Try it.
- Help me, son.

01:19:21.750 --> 01:19:27.125
My wife's ill. The hospital wants
a deposit of 10,000 rupees.

01:19:27.208 --> 01:19:31.458
I'm short of 500.
Please help me...

01:19:31.541 --> 01:19:33.166
Let me give you some money.

01:19:34.375 --> 01:19:36.333
Here.
- Give me your address.

01:19:36.458 --> 01:19:37.916
I'll courier a check.

01:19:38.000 --> 01:19:41.500
The courier won't reach my home.
Please keep it.

01:19:41.583 --> 01:19:43.041
Thank you.

01:19:43.958 --> 01:19:45.083
Sir.

01:19:45.708 --> 01:19:48.750
Here's another 100.
For the tip.

01:19:50.916 --> 01:19:53.000
Bless you.

01:19:54.125 --> 01:19:58.000
This proves that you're no mind reader.

01:19:58.333 --> 01:20:03.416
You got conned.
There is no hospital around here.

01:20:03.625 --> 01:20:04.916
I know!

01:20:05.125 --> 01:20:07.958
He's gifting his wife a five star dinner.

01:20:08.041 --> 01:20:10.166
It's her 75th birthday.

01:20:10.250 --> 01:20:13.041
She has never been to a fancy place.

01:20:13.250 --> 01:20:16.083
He's been saving from
his pension for months.

01:20:16.208 --> 01:20:19.583
She ordered ice-cream
and his budget went kaput.

01:20:19.666 --> 01:20:22.541
With an excuse to go to the restroom,
he ran out for some bucks.

01:20:22.625 --> 01:20:24.166
Another yarn!

01:20:25.250 --> 01:20:28.458
Ma'am, on my planet, we don't lie!

01:20:29.416 --> 01:20:31.166
Anyway, it's up to you.

01:21:31.625 --> 01:21:33.208
Here.
- Thank you, Sir.

01:21:33.291 --> 01:21:36.083
One moment. Tip him.

01:21:36.166 --> 01:21:40.791
Why hold back?
It's your birthday!

01:21:40.875 --> 01:21:41.958
Thank you.

01:22:11.208 --> 01:22:13.083
'Contact: Tipsy,
The Agrasen Step-Well.'

01:22:37.291 --> 01:22:39.500
I told you.
On my planet, we don't lie.

01:22:42.541 --> 01:22:43.916
Hope you haven't told anyone...

01:22:51.791 --> 01:22:54.041
Have you told anyone that you're an alien?

01:22:54.125 --> 01:22:55.291
No way!

01:22:55.500 --> 01:23:00.208
They'd lock me in a lab,
and rip me up for research!

01:23:02.083 --> 01:23:04.875
How come you told me?

01:23:06.416 --> 01:23:08.041
Ever since I set foot on this planet

01:23:08.166 --> 01:23:11.333
everyone has taken money from me.

01:23:11.541 --> 01:23:15.208
You were the first to give up
5000 rupees for me.

01:23:15.625 --> 01:23:19.208
I thought you are a good egg.
I could trust you.

01:23:22.541 --> 01:23:24.791
I'll get your remote back, Tipsy.

01:23:26.250 --> 01:23:27.791
How?

01:23:28.125 --> 01:23:32.291
I haven't figured it out yet,
but you'll go back home.

01:24:21.375 --> 01:24:23.458
What are you goggling at?

01:24:23.958 --> 01:24:25.000
You.

01:24:25.958 --> 01:24:28.250
Aliens don't drop by my house everyday.

01:24:29.500 --> 01:24:33.791
Does everyone on your planet
have stick-out ears?

01:24:36.541 --> 01:24:40.166
Yup, ditto.
- And everyone roams around naked?

01:24:40.791 --> 01:24:42.000
Isn't it weird?

01:24:43.166 --> 01:24:46.750
That crow is naked.
Does it look weird?

01:24:47.041 --> 01:24:49.333
But if it dons a tie,
it'd definitely look weird.

01:24:52.416 --> 01:24:55.500
Tipsy, I was up all night...

01:24:56.333 --> 01:24:59.500
thinking how to get your remote back.

01:25:00.166 --> 01:25:01.125
Hello?

01:25:01.208 --> 01:25:04.041
'Hello. Connect to Balbir Singh.
Room no. 4.'

01:25:04.500 --> 01:25:05.833
Wrong number!

01:25:06.125 --> 01:25:07.750
'Isn't it the Fortis Hospital?'

01:25:08.000 --> 01:25:10.833
You've been dialing the wrong
number since yesterday.

01:25:10.916 --> 01:25:14.666
'Impossible!
I can't be wrong every time!'

01:25:15.791 --> 01:25:17.500
So how do we get the remote?

01:25:21.958 --> 01:25:24.791
'Hello, connect to Balbir Singh.
Room no. 4.'

01:25:24.875 --> 01:25:28.041
Sorry, Sir. You're late.
- 'What happened?'

01:25:28.125 --> 01:25:29.958
Balbir died this morning.

01:25:30.375 --> 01:25:34.625
'What! How can a piles surgery be fatal?'

01:25:34.875 --> 01:25:37.458
It is embarrassing,
but don't worry.

01:25:37.666 --> 01:25:39.875
We'll have "heart attack" written
on the death certificate.

01:25:39.958 --> 01:25:42.083
It shouldn't spoil
the family's reputation.

01:25:42.291 --> 01:25:44.500
Come for the body.
- 'On my way.'

01:25:44.666 --> 01:25:46.041
Okay, bye.
- 'Get the car...'

01:25:49.375 --> 01:25:50.875
Why did you say that?

01:25:51.083 --> 01:25:52.583
I'm doling out joy.

01:25:52.666 --> 01:25:56.750
When he finds his friend alive,
imagine his joy!

01:25:56.833 --> 01:25:57.875
What!

01:25:57.958 --> 01:26:02.500
I was sick of his calls.
So I played a prank.

01:26:02.666 --> 01:26:05.916
A prank?
- Tipsy, I was just kidding!

01:26:12.708 --> 01:26:13.833
Oh!

01:26:15.333 --> 01:26:18.625
I got it! Someone is playing pranks.

01:26:18.958 --> 01:26:21.458
When His Holiness dials God,

01:26:21.750 --> 01:26:24.958
cocking his head,
"God, enlighten me."

01:26:25.291 --> 01:26:27.458
His calls are going to a wrong number.

01:26:28.166 --> 01:26:30.750
Someone out there is playing pranks.

01:26:30.958 --> 01:26:35.041
The real God wouldn't
call my remote a bead.

01:26:36.416 --> 01:26:43.083
Looks like the phone lines
to God have gone kaput.

01:26:43.375 --> 01:26:45.833
All calls to God are going
to a wrong number!

01:26:46.208 --> 01:26:48.333
As in?
- I always used to think,

01:26:48.666 --> 01:26:52.041
why would the real God
give such weird solutions?

01:26:52.458 --> 01:26:56.333
Why would He say,
"come rolling to me, then I'll help you!"?

01:26:56.750 --> 01:26:59.125
Aren't we God's children?

01:26:59.416 --> 01:27:04.625
Would a father make his kids
roll for help?

01:27:05.000 --> 01:27:06.416
I'm sure your dad would've never said

01:27:06.541 --> 01:27:10.125
"Kiddo, you want a new dress?
Start rolling!"

01:27:10.875 --> 01:27:15.333
Why would He want to bathe in milk?
That's illogical!

01:27:16.000 --> 01:27:22.041
And if these calls went to
the real God, what would He say?

01:27:22.250 --> 01:27:27.000
He'd say, "millions of my children
are starving on the streets.

01:27:27.291 --> 01:27:30.333
Give them milk.
Don't give me a lactose shower."

01:27:30.791 --> 01:27:34.375
I'm sure someone's playing
pranks, like you did.

01:27:35.291 --> 01:27:37.791
'Tipsy thought His Holiness
was a victim of pranks.'

01:27:38.041 --> 01:27:39.958
'I didn't clear his confusion...'

01:27:40.291 --> 01:27:43.125
'for a crazy idea was forming in my head.'

01:27:43.250 --> 01:27:46.500
'An idea that would
get back Tipsy's remote.'

01:27:48.291 --> 01:27:49.375
Who's this Tipsy?

01:27:49.916 --> 01:27:51.833
That's a mystery.

01:27:52.083 --> 01:27:54.500
But the way he sees this world is unique.

01:27:55.250 --> 01:27:58.500
As in?
- If he saw you smoking,

01:27:58.791 --> 01:28:01.333
he'd call the cops to say
that you're attempting suicide.

01:28:01.541 --> 01:28:02.375
Why?

01:28:02.458 --> 01:28:04.583
The pack says "Smoking kills"
yet you puff away.

01:28:06.833 --> 01:28:08.833
So what's the big idea?

01:28:10.583 --> 01:28:11.958
Face-off.

01:28:12.291 --> 01:28:15.125
Between Tipsy and His Holiness.

01:28:15.541 --> 01:28:18.208
We'll take the face-off to TV.

01:28:18.750 --> 01:28:21.083
Ratings will go through the roof!
- Jaggu.

01:28:21.875 --> 01:28:24.666
I have three trident marks
on my right bum.

01:28:25.083 --> 01:28:27.750
You want three more on
my left for balance?

01:28:29.250 --> 01:28:34.250
Tipsy won't fight His Holiness,
but gently explain, that...

01:28:34.666 --> 01:28:37.708
his calls to God
are going to a wrong number.

01:28:38.208 --> 01:28:40.625
His Holiness will be stumped.

01:28:44.000 --> 01:28:46.208
Tipsy's here.
Please meet him once.

01:28:46.625 --> 01:28:49.125
I bet his queries will baffle you.

01:29:01.666 --> 01:29:03.541
Excuse me, you dropped this.

01:29:08.666 --> 01:29:10.875
That's not mine.

01:29:12.166 --> 01:29:14.333
Kamasutra condoms,
strawberry flavor.

01:29:16.333 --> 01:29:19.416
I hate strawberries, man.
Why don't you ask others?

01:29:19.541 --> 01:29:22.041
It's not mine.
Buzzed bozo!

01:29:24.333 --> 01:29:25.375
Is this yours, Ma'am?

01:29:26.750 --> 01:29:30.333
Check your purse if it's missing.
- Shameless cad!

01:29:32.041 --> 01:29:34.708
Has to be yours.
- No, not mine.

01:29:34.791 --> 01:29:36.708
Tipsy, it's his.

01:29:37.166 --> 01:29:40.500
Ask him about it. Come on in.

01:29:42.166 --> 01:29:43.208
Come in.

01:29:45.916 --> 01:29:47.125
What's this?

01:29:48.250 --> 01:29:49.833
It's a condom.

01:29:50.083 --> 01:29:53.625
What does it do?
- It controls the world's population.

01:29:55.458 --> 01:29:56.500
How?

01:29:56.958 --> 01:30:01.333
It has to be worn... while having sex.

01:30:03.625 --> 01:30:06.833
How does your wearing it
control the world's population?

01:30:06.916 --> 01:30:10.166
Not just me.
Millions wear it.

01:30:10.333 --> 01:30:12.333
And they all borrow it from you?

01:30:12.875 --> 01:30:14.125
Everyone has it.

01:30:14.750 --> 01:30:17.958
I've a question.
- Go on, Tipsy.

01:30:18.750 --> 01:30:23.125
When money is dropped, all run for it.

01:30:23.250 --> 01:30:27.583
But when a condom is dropped,
all run away from it. Why?

01:30:29.083 --> 01:30:32.333
Sex is a very private matter.
- Why?

01:30:32.791 --> 01:30:35.708
You don't announce it to the world saying
"I'm having sex today."

01:30:37.041 --> 01:30:41.541
But, at weddings,
with fireworks and music bands,

01:30:41.875 --> 01:30:45.208
why do they tell the whole town,
"I'm having sex today"?

01:30:49.083 --> 01:30:50.500
What's the matter?

01:30:51.000 --> 01:30:55.583
I have no answer for you
but I have a job for you.

01:30:59.666 --> 01:31:02.166
Let's beat it before
he changes his mind.

01:31:05.083 --> 01:31:09.000
Shield your holy bum, Your Holiness.
My trident is on its way.

01:31:13.750 --> 01:31:17.208
Tipsy, here His Holiness
connects his devotees to God

01:31:17.291 --> 01:31:19.166
for solutions to their woes.

01:31:19.541 --> 01:31:22.375
Listen carefully to his calls.

01:31:22.500 --> 01:31:28.875
If you think the calls are going
to a wrong number, alert him.

01:31:29.208 --> 01:31:32.750
Will that get me my remote?
- Once he realizes

01:31:32.875 --> 01:31:37.500
that the bead story is a prank,
he'll return your remote.

01:31:37.625 --> 01:31:40.333
Good plan. Let's go.

01:31:42.083 --> 01:31:45.083
'To build a home for someone
is a holy deed.'

01:31:45.166 --> 01:31:49.833
To build a home for God
is the holiest deed.

01:31:50.208 --> 01:31:52.458
So donate for the temple.

01:31:53.125 --> 01:31:55.958
And see your woes flee.

01:31:56.708 --> 01:32:00.250
Son, voice your woe.

01:32:01.208 --> 01:32:02.625
Your Holiness,

01:32:03.250 --> 01:32:05.791
my wife's been paralyzed
for six months.

01:32:06.125 --> 01:32:09.791
The doctors have given up.
What should I--

01:32:11.375 --> 01:32:12.916
God...

01:32:13.666 --> 01:32:15.041
enlighten me.

01:32:22.125 --> 01:32:23.541
Yes.

01:32:26.833 --> 01:32:28.250
What place?

01:32:33.875 --> 01:32:35.500
What transport?

01:32:38.458 --> 01:32:40.750
Your wish is our command.

01:32:43.500 --> 01:32:46.083
Have you heard of
the Rathong glacier?

01:32:46.166 --> 01:32:47.375
No.

01:32:47.791 --> 01:32:52.250
It's in the Himalayas.
Take a train to Silliguri...

01:32:53.083 --> 01:32:55.875
then a bus to Gangtok.

01:32:56.666 --> 01:33:01.208
Then an eight day trek.

01:33:01.875 --> 01:33:06.000
You'll reach a grand temple.

01:33:07.333 --> 01:33:10.541
Pray there,
your problem will be solved.

01:33:10.666 --> 01:33:13.125
Wrong number!
This is a wrong number!

01:33:13.458 --> 01:33:15.291
What?
- Wrong number!

01:33:15.625 --> 01:33:20.958
Your Holiness, your phone line
to God has gone kaput.

01:33:21.583 --> 01:33:23.791
Your calls are going to
a wrong number

01:33:24.041 --> 01:33:27.833
and a fake God is playing pranks.

01:33:28.000 --> 01:33:31.208
What are you trying to say?

01:33:31.541 --> 01:33:34.416
I'll explain.
Aren't we God's children?

01:33:35.083 --> 01:33:36.125
Yes, so?

01:33:36.250 --> 01:33:39.958
If your kid's in trouble
and asks for a solution

01:33:40.375 --> 01:33:43.041
would you help him promptly,
or would you say,

01:33:43.208 --> 01:33:46.541
"Kiddo, I've another house
2,000 miles away.

01:33:46.708 --> 01:33:49.750
Come there and tell me
the same problem again.

01:33:50.041 --> 01:33:52.458
Then I'll solve it."
What bull!

01:33:52.750 --> 01:33:54.750
If the call went to the real God,

01:33:54.875 --> 01:33:58.166
He'd say, "Son, tend to your ailing wife.

01:33:58.375 --> 01:34:00.708
Don't run after me.

01:34:01.000 --> 01:34:03.958
After death, you'll come to me anyway.

01:34:04.125 --> 01:34:07.750
Give her your time now."
Right?

01:34:12.000 --> 01:34:14.541
I can prove it's a prank.

01:34:14.708 --> 01:34:18.000
Call this fake God again and ask,

01:34:18.166 --> 01:34:20.833
what's the guarantee
that she will get well.

01:34:20.958 --> 01:34:25.208
Sir, don't leave her side
till you get it in writing.

01:34:25.291 --> 01:34:28.375
Just call, and clear all the doubts.

01:34:29.250 --> 01:34:32.625
It's time for His Holiness' holy silence.

