01:57:12.166 --> 01:57:16.833
'I knew that you were on the
wrong track. But I kept mum.'

01:57:16.916 --> 01:57:20.833
'If you would've called him a fraud,
people would've killed you.'

01:57:21.125 --> 01:57:23.166
'People crave for the unique.'

01:57:23.333 --> 01:57:25.000
'Wrong number!'

01:57:25.250 --> 01:57:28.291
'Your "wrong number" concept was unique.'

01:57:28.375 --> 01:57:31.083
'Today the world supports you.
- This is a wrong number.'

01:57:31.166 --> 01:57:34.458
Tipsy, my plan worked!
You're going home!

01:57:40.375 --> 01:57:43.916
You'll fly away tomorrow, my friend.

01:57:48.458 --> 01:57:51.291
We'll never meet again.

01:57:52.833 --> 01:57:56.041
There will be such a void.

01:58:01.791 --> 01:58:03.875
Should I stay back?

01:58:06.625 --> 01:58:08.500
How can you?

01:58:10.041 --> 01:58:12.916
I'm serious.
I have a job.

01:58:13.875 --> 01:58:16.750
I'll get some ID made
and settle here.

01:58:17.375 --> 01:58:21.708
I'll find someone to
"waste time" with me.

01:58:22.208 --> 01:58:24.750
I'll marry her.

01:58:24.958 --> 01:58:27.916
Who will marry you?
- Why not?

01:58:28.041 --> 01:58:32.541
Your wife will go nuts
introducing you.

01:58:33.125 --> 01:58:36.666
"Meet my husband.
He's Tipsy!"

01:58:37.916 --> 01:58:41.166
That's not my name!
Nonsense!

01:58:41.250 --> 01:58:44.041
Tipsy!
- I'll get a real name.

01:58:45.208 --> 01:58:51.083
Why don't you suggest one?
A name you like.

01:58:51.666 --> 01:58:57.500
A man's name must
match his personality.

01:58:57.625 --> 01:58:59.250
Right!

01:58:59.500 --> 01:59:02.083
So how is my personality?

01:59:02.333 --> 01:59:04.333
Let me give you a demo.

01:59:04.833 --> 01:59:06.958
A poet once wrote...

01:59:09.291 --> 01:59:12.375
'Irony of mismatched names.'

01:59:12.458 --> 01:59:15.791
No poetry, please!
I've something to say.

01:59:16.333 --> 01:59:20.708
'Who says,
"What's in a name?"'

01:59:20.791 --> 01:59:22.000
How do I make her understand?

01:59:22.375 --> 01:59:26.208
'If you don't get the right one
what a pain.'

01:59:27.083 --> 01:59:31.000
'Mr. Burns is in fact so cool.'

01:59:31.333 --> 01:59:34.541
'With violence alone Mr. Peace does rule.'

01:59:35.666 --> 01:59:41.291
'His name is Mr. Fox
but has no bushy tail.'

01:59:42.166 --> 01:59:45.625
'The name is Mr. Green,
but he's always pale.'

01:59:46.875 --> 01:59:51.333
'One whole ton
is the weight of Mr. Flower.'

01:59:51.708 --> 01:59:55.666
'At his mere sight,
the poor chair does cower.'

01:59:55.750 --> 01:59:57.541
Very nice. Very nice.

01:59:57.625 --> 02:00:00.750
Here's a bunch of cards
with different names.

02:00:01.541 --> 02:00:05.125
Pick the one you like.

02:00:05.208 --> 02:00:08.000
Danduram Thatte?

02:00:08.416 --> 02:00:10.916
Disaster!
- Next!

02:00:11.458 --> 02:00:13.166
Tutari Singh?

02:00:16.416 --> 02:00:18.041
Sarfaraz...

02:00:22.375 --> 02:00:25.041
Sarfaraz.
- What happened?

02:00:25.291 --> 02:00:28.083
Keep going,
find a good name.

02:00:31.458 --> 02:00:33.083
What's the matter?

02:00:33.666 --> 02:00:35.291
Nothing.

02:01:43.708 --> 02:01:45.458
Brother!

02:02:18.083 --> 02:02:21.791
"God is in His Heaven,
we mortals on ground."

02:02:22.125 --> 02:02:25.541
"God is in His Heaven,
we mortals on ground."

02:02:26.000 --> 02:02:30.125
"Nowadays He doesn't have
Time to look around."

02:02:30.250 --> 02:02:34.541
"God is in His Heaven,
we mortals on ground."

02:02:42.250 --> 02:02:46.083
"Whatever may happen here
He does not reprimand..."

02:02:46.208 --> 02:02:50.375
"Thousand evils, million wrongs...
He does not take a stand..."

02:02:50.458 --> 02:02:54.125
"Plundering is all around.
Bombs come to hound..."

02:03:42.333 --> 02:03:45.833
'A terrorist outfit has claimed
responsibility for the blast.'

02:03:45.916 --> 02:03:49.333
'They say, "This was a mock drill.

02:03:49.625 --> 02:03:52.541
Persecute our people,
and real war will follow.

02:03:52.625 --> 02:03:55.791
We shall protect our God."'

02:04:17.000 --> 02:04:19.208
Where are you going, Tipsy?

02:04:20.000 --> 02:04:21.250
On the show.

02:04:21.541 --> 02:04:23.625
You don't have to.

02:04:25.875 --> 02:04:28.458
I must, more than ever.

02:04:42.875 --> 02:04:44.291
The Final Question.

02:04:44.833 --> 02:04:48.250
Welcome to our special show

02:04:48.333 --> 02:04:52.000
where we'll meet Tipsy and...
- Wait a minute.

02:04:57.875 --> 02:04:59.875
Bring it.

02:05:05.375 --> 02:05:07.250
What is this?

02:05:07.458 --> 02:05:12.125
God says, it's a divine bead
from His necklace.

02:05:12.375 --> 02:05:16.041
This man claims, it's his property.

02:05:16.791 --> 02:05:20.291
God says, build a temple.

02:05:20.708 --> 02:05:24.083
And this man opposes it.

02:05:24.416 --> 02:05:29.958
Who should I listen to?
God, or this gentleman

02:05:30.208 --> 02:05:36.125
who used to hand out these
blasphemous pamphlets?

02:05:37.458 --> 02:05:40.500
'First he claimed, God is missing.'

02:05:41.166 --> 02:05:43.166
'Then said, God is a fraud.'

02:05:43.416 --> 02:05:47.166
Next he'll say, God is dead.

02:05:48.625 --> 02:05:54.166
What do you want, son?
A world without God?

02:05:56.291 --> 02:06:00.833
Do you have any clue how people suffer?

02:06:01.250 --> 02:06:03.541
People have no food to eat...

02:06:04.083 --> 02:06:06.083
no place to live.

02:06:07.041 --> 02:06:09.791
No friend to talk to.

02:06:10.291 --> 02:06:16.875
People kill themselves.
Slit their wrists, jump off buildings.

02:06:17.458 --> 02:06:21.333
Why? Because they have no hope.

02:06:21.708 --> 02:06:26.291
If bowing before God,
smearing holy ash,

02:06:26.958 --> 02:06:31.708
wearing amulets,
gives them hope to live,

02:06:32.000 --> 02:06:36.125
then who are you
to snatch away that hope?

02:06:37.375 --> 02:06:41.833
And if you snatch away their God,

02:06:42.041 --> 02:06:45.541
how will you fill that void?

02:06:46.291 --> 02:06:50.333
This man rants about wrong numbers.

02:06:50.791 --> 02:06:55.375
Today he must tell us,
what is the right number.

02:07:04.416 --> 02:07:06.750
You are right, Your Holiness.

02:07:08.208 --> 02:07:13.791
There was a time
when I too had no food to eat.

02:07:14.500 --> 02:07:16.333
No place to live.

02:07:16.875 --> 02:07:21.958
I used to cry a lot
because I had no friend.

02:07:23.375 --> 02:07:26.625
The only thing I had, was hope.

02:07:29.000 --> 02:07:30.916
God.

02:07:31.750 --> 02:07:35.083
Each day I hoped,
tomorrow will be better.

02:07:35.375 --> 02:07:38.208
God will find a solution.

02:07:39.750 --> 02:07:46.708
I agree that believing
in God gives hope...

02:07:47.916 --> 02:07:52.208
the strength to face ordeals.

02:07:53.333 --> 02:07:55.875
But I have one question.

02:07:58.666 --> 02:08:01.625
Which God should I believe in?

02:08:02.583 --> 02:08:05.250
You say there is one God.

02:08:06.875 --> 02:08:08.833
I say no.

02:08:09.833 --> 02:08:11.375
There are two Gods.

02:08:12.875 --> 02:08:15.041
One who created us.

02:08:16.583 --> 02:08:20.375
And the other, whom you created.

02:08:21.583 --> 02:08:24.708
We know nothing about
the God who made us.

02:08:25.166 --> 02:08:29.875
But the God you made up,
is just like you.

02:08:30.250 --> 02:08:34.750
Petty. Takes bribes,
makes false promises.

02:08:34.916 --> 02:08:38.958
Readily meets the rich,
keeps the poor waiting.

02:08:39.250 --> 02:08:42.625
Thrives on flattery.
Makes you live in fear.

02:08:44.625 --> 02:08:46.916
My right number is simple.

02:08:48.333 --> 02:08:53.041
Believe in the God who created us.

02:08:54.708 --> 02:08:58.083
And the God you created...

02:08:59.000 --> 02:09:01.208
should be abolished.

02:09:03.208 --> 02:09:07.416
You'll abolish my God
and I'll keep quiet?

02:09:07.708 --> 02:09:11.791
I know how to protect my God.

02:09:11.875 --> 02:09:13.875
You will protect God?

02:09:14.333 --> 02:09:15.458
You!

02:09:16.708 --> 02:09:18.416
This is a puny planet.

02:09:19.000 --> 02:09:21.875
Billions of bigger planets
float in the space.

02:09:22.083 --> 02:09:26.875
And you, sitting in a tiny corner of this
puny planet, have the nerve to say

02:09:27.083 --> 02:09:30.750
that you will protect Him?
The creator of the universe!

02:09:31.833 --> 02:09:36.541
He doesn't need your protection.
He can protect Himself.

02:09:40.083 --> 02:09:45.583
Today someone tried to
protect their God and my friend died.

02:09:46.541 --> 02:09:48.291
This is all that's left, his shoe.

02:09:50.125 --> 02:09:52.291
Stop protecting God.

02:09:52.833 --> 02:09:56.291
Or else this planet will have
no humans, only shoes.

02:09:56.541 --> 02:09:58.958
A Muslim terrorist blows up a train

02:09:59.875 --> 02:10:05.291
and a Hindu guru endures
your sermon. That's nice.

02:10:05.541 --> 02:10:10.458
What's this Hindu, Muslim?
Show me the label.

02:10:11.708 --> 02:10:14.416
You created these differences, not God.

02:10:15.083 --> 02:10:21.041
This is the deadliest
wrong number of this planet.

02:10:21.333 --> 02:10:24.000
It kills people, separates them.

02:10:24.458 --> 02:10:29.375
Like your wrong number
separated Jaggu from Sarfaraz.

02:10:29.458 --> 02:10:35.500
What wrong number?
- That Sarfaraz would betray her.

02:10:35.833 --> 02:10:38.375
And he did betray her.

02:10:38.458 --> 02:10:42.958
Hold on. What's going on?
- Hold it.

02:10:44.875 --> 02:10:52.125
Are you telling me that my prophecy
about Sarfaraz was wrong?

02:10:52.208 --> 02:10:53.458
Exactly!

02:10:53.541 --> 02:10:57.708
Then prove it.
Prove my prophecy wrong!

02:10:57.791 --> 02:11:02.416
And if you fail,
you'll have to fall at my feet and admit

02:11:02.541 --> 02:11:06.583
that you are a liar.
And that you tried to defame me.

02:11:07.208 --> 02:11:09.416
What if I prove it?

02:11:09.500 --> 02:11:10.791
No, Tipsy!

02:11:17.333 --> 02:11:19.000
Then this shall be yours.

02:11:24.958 --> 02:11:26.583
I accept.

02:11:27.083 --> 02:11:31.791
Turn the cameras towards
Jagat Janani.

02:11:37.916 --> 02:11:44.583
I hope you will answer
my questions truthfully.

02:11:47.000 --> 02:11:52.083
In Belgium you fell in love
with a Pakistani boy.

02:11:53.541 --> 02:11:54.875
True or false?

02:11:55.250 --> 02:11:57.416
Please spare my personal life.

02:11:57.583 --> 02:12:01.916
On Friday, at 3:21 p.m.

02:12:02.000 --> 02:12:06.250
I predicted that this
boy will betray you.

02:12:06.583 --> 02:12:10.958
The next day you went to the
Marriage Registrar's office

02:12:11.375 --> 02:12:13.250
'but he didn't show up.'

02:12:13.708 --> 02:12:17.083
True or false?
- Yes, he didn't come.

02:12:17.166 --> 02:12:18.833
Can you please stop this?

02:12:20.916 --> 02:12:27.250
Now will you come to my feet
or should I walk up to you?

02:12:27.333 --> 02:12:31.416
Sarfaraz did not betray.
- Please let it go!

02:12:31.500 --> 02:12:33.791
No. Tell us what happened that day.

02:12:34.166 --> 02:12:35.791
Tipsy, please!

02:12:35.875 --> 02:12:39.166
Just once, for my sake.

02:12:44.333 --> 02:12:47.500
I was at the
Marriage Registrar's office and...

02:12:48.875 --> 02:12:51.291
I received a letter.
- Did Sarfaraz bring it?

02:12:53.875 --> 02:12:58.083
No. He sent it through a kid.

02:12:58.166 --> 02:13:01.250
Was it signed?
- No!

02:13:01.333 --> 02:13:04.291
Then how do you know
that Sarfaraz sent it?

02:13:08.250 --> 02:13:11.083
It could have been for some other girl.

02:13:15.208 --> 02:13:19.625
There was another girl.
With a cat, right?

02:13:21.541 --> 02:13:25.791
She asked you to hold the
cat for a while, right?

02:13:26.625 --> 02:13:29.666
The kid who gave you the letter,
did he know you?

02:13:30.500 --> 02:13:33.041
No.
- Did you know him?

02:13:34.000 --> 02:13:34.833
No.

02:13:34.916 --> 02:13:38.500
Then how would he know
that the letter was for you?

02:13:39.875 --> 02:13:46.500
Maybe he was told to give
the letter to the girl with the cat.

02:13:48.541 --> 02:13:54.291
You read the letter,
but didn't call Sarfaraz.

02:13:55.750 --> 02:13:57.958
Did you?

02:13:58.708 --> 02:14:02.750
Because this man planted
a wrong number in your head

02:14:03.166 --> 02:14:05.916
that Muslims betray.

02:14:06.000 --> 02:14:08.375
Sarfaraz didn't betray you, Jaggu.

02:14:08.458 --> 02:14:09.791
What's going on?

02:14:10.291 --> 02:14:15.208
You expect us to believe
these cat and bull stories?

02:14:15.333 --> 02:14:16.666
One minute.

02:14:17.000 --> 02:14:21.000
We'll get to the truth right now.
Jaggu, call Sarfaraz.

02:14:25.625 --> 02:14:28.833
'This number does not exist.'

02:14:29.875 --> 02:14:30.958
Any other number?

02:14:31.125 --> 02:14:33.291
Friend, college, something...

02:14:33.583 --> 02:14:34.875
Come on, Jaggu!

02:14:35.000 --> 02:14:36.458
Belgium University.
- Dial.

02:14:41.125 --> 02:14:42.791
Hello.
- Hello...

02:14:43.708 --> 02:14:46.875
I actually need to get in touch
with one of your grad students.

02:14:47.583 --> 02:14:48.875
Sarfaraz Yousuf.

02:14:48.958 --> 02:14:51.208
Oh, yeah, he left for Pakistan
last year.

02:14:51.250 --> 02:14:52.500
Contact?

02:14:52.583 --> 02:14:53.625
Has he left a number?

02:14:53.708 --> 02:14:56.541
I'm sorry, we're not authorized
to give out information.

02:14:56.750 --> 02:14:58.291
Ma'am, this is really important.

02:14:58.375 --> 02:13:59.083
'Email us your request, so I can
forward it to student affairs.'

02:13:59.166 --> 02:14:00.583
Have a nice day, dear.

02:15:03.166 --> 02:15:05.625
What about his home phone number?
- I don't know.

02:15:05.708 --> 02:15:08.208
Think, Jaggu darling, think...

02:15:09.166 --> 02:15:11.666
'I work at the Pakistan Embassy.'

02:15:12.166 --> 02:15:14.375
He used to work at the Pakistan Embassy.

02:15:15.458 --> 02:15:17.791
Mitu, call the Pakistan Embassy, Belgium.

02:15:17.875 --> 02:15:19.583
Copy, sir.
- 'Put it on the speakers.'

02:15:23.541 --> 02:15:25.416
Greetings.
Pakistan Embassy.

02:15:26.000 --> 02:15:26.958
Hello...

02:15:29.125 --> 02:15:32.458
A student from Lahore worked with you.

02:15:32.583 --> 02:15:33.708
Sarfaraz Yousuf.

02:15:33.833 --> 02:15:35.333
Is your name Jaggu?

02:15:39.000 --> 02:15:41.500
Hello. Is your name Jaggu?

02:15:41.916 --> 02:15:43.625
Yes. How do you know?

02:15:43.916 --> 02:15:45.250
She called!

02:15:45.375 --> 02:15:47.666
The girl from Delhi has called!

02:15:47.791 --> 02:15:49.500
Farah, it's Jaggu calling!

02:15:49.583 --> 02:15:53.416
Mr. Sayyed, hurry up.
It's Jaggu's call from India.

02:15:53.500 --> 02:15:55.750
Come on, hurry up!
Everyone!

02:15:58.791 --> 02:16:04.625
Sarfaraz Yousuf calls us from Lahore,
every day at 9:00 a.m.

02:16:05.416 --> 02:16:09.541
and with impeccable politeness,
asks just one question.

02:16:09.833 --> 02:16:13.958
"Did Jaggu call from India?"

02:16:14.875 --> 02:16:18.000
We say "no," and he disconnects.

02:16:18.250 --> 02:16:20.125
He's driven us crazy.

02:16:20.375 --> 02:16:22.750
Wait. Let me connect you.

02:16:38.083 --> 02:16:39.416
'Hello?'

02:16:40.333 --> 02:16:43.583
Mr. Sarfaraz Yousuf?
- 'Yes, speaking.'

02:16:43.958 --> 02:16:47.833
Where are you?
- 'In Lahore. Why?'

02:16:48.208 --> 02:16:53.208
Where are you right now?
- 'At home. Why?'

02:16:53.750 --> 02:16:57.500
Is there a chair or a bench nearby?

02:16:57.833 --> 02:17:02.083
Please sit down.
You're about to get a jolt.

02:17:03.375 --> 02:17:05.375
'Pardon me?'

02:17:06.916 --> 02:17:08.458
You have a call from Delhi.

02:17:15.541 --> 02:17:17.458
Here, talk to her.

02:17:20.041 --> 02:17:21.125
Hello?

02:17:21.375 --> 02:17:23.250
Sarfaraz.

02:17:27.458 --> 02:17:29.125
Jaggu.

02:17:33.791 --> 02:17:35.916
Hello, Jaggu, what's the matter?

02:17:38.833 --> 02:17:41.083
Did you go to the
Marriage Registrar's office?

02:17:41.208 --> 02:17:45.041
I did, but you had left.

02:17:45.708 --> 02:17:47.750
Why didn't you call?

02:17:48.041 --> 02:17:50.250
How could I?
I got your letter.

02:17:50.708 --> 02:17:53.333
'You had said, "don't contact me."'

02:17:54.208 --> 02:17:56.750
I knew you were under family pressure.

02:17:56.833 --> 02:18:03.333
But deep down I knew,
one day you would contact me.

02:18:05.666 --> 02:18:08.000
What took you so long?

02:18:09.833 --> 02:18:14.291
I am sorry.
I had your wrong number.

02:18:21.666 --> 02:18:24.166
I just got the right
number from a friend.

02:18:51.666 --> 02:18:53.041
Thank you, son.

02:19:28.083 --> 02:19:29.916
Here, hold this.

02:19:54.208 --> 02:19:57.250
Tipsy! You're taking batteries home?

02:19:57.916 --> 02:20:02.416
Don't get them there.
- But why do you need so many batteries?

02:20:02.708 --> 02:20:06.625
Back home, I'll listen
to the sounds I've recorded.

02:20:06.958 --> 02:20:08.291
What sounds?

02:20:08.583 --> 02:20:12.958
The sounds of earth.
Of the crows, the traffic, the honking.

02:20:13.166 --> 02:20:15.541
Up there, you'll listen to cars honking?

02:20:15.833 --> 02:20:20.375
Now and then...
whenever I miss this planet.

02:20:22.916 --> 02:20:26.500
Hey, wait!
There's one more bag.

02:20:26.583 --> 02:20:28.125
Forget it, Tipsy!

02:20:28.208 --> 02:20:31.666
You kidding?
It's stuffed with batteries.

02:20:32.125 --> 02:20:33.875
Wait!

02:20:37.583 --> 02:20:41.000
Driver, please stop!

02:20:54.625 --> 02:20:58.375
'Does everyone on your planet
have stick-out ears?'

02:20:59.625 --> 02:21:02.791
'And everyone roams around naked?'

02:21:04.250 --> 02:21:06.791
'Why are you staring?
Is there something on my face?'

02:21:11.375 --> 02:21:13.958
'You know, I was in tenth grade...'

02:21:15.000 --> 02:21:16.750
'when I wrote my first poem.'

02:21:18.416 --> 02:21:20.416
'It was for Papa.'

02:21:21.375 --> 02:21:26.875
'"They say my Mom I resemble.
I say, possible."'

02:21:34.166 --> 02:21:38.125
'Poetry means
sparse words, soaring thoughts.'

02:21:40.500 --> 02:21:42.583
'Pal, you're really cute.'

02:21:44.291 --> 02:21:47.791
'Here's to the teetotaler called Tipsy.'

02:21:48.666 --> 02:21:52.583
'Granted, I am poor...'

02:21:53.583 --> 02:21:57.750
'No tape had the sounds of
the crows or the traffic.'

02:21:58.416 --> 02:22:00.916
'Every tape had just my voice.'

02:22:11.791 --> 02:22:12.833
'Mandawa'

02:22:15.750 --> 02:22:17.500
Got it!

02:22:22.541 --> 02:22:25.083
He sure made me run!

02:22:28.333 --> 02:22:31.625
Tipsy, what's in these tapes?

02:22:32.875 --> 02:22:35.375
I told you.
The crows, the traffic.

02:22:47.625 --> 02:22:52.083
Every night, when your planet
rises, I'll play these tapes.

02:22:53.458 --> 02:22:58.708
And wave at you.
Like this.

02:23:01.208 --> 02:23:04.750
Will you wave back,
now and then?

02:23:07.000 --> 02:23:09.416
Haven't you recorded my voice?

02:23:10.458 --> 02:23:12.958
Your voice?

02:23:13.291 --> 02:23:17.500
I think I have.
That one poem you recited.

02:23:18.625 --> 02:23:21.333
One poem? That's all?

02:23:24.458 --> 02:23:26.999
I'm not exactly in love with you,

02:23:27.250 --> 02:23:28.833
to waste all my time over you!

02:23:49.208 --> 02:23:52.083
'He didn't look back.
Not once.'

02:23:52.750 --> 02:23:54.583
'Perhaps, he was hiding his tears.'

02:23:55.916 --> 02:23:59.833
'One thing he learnt from us.
One thing he taught us.'

02:24:01.250 --> 02:24:03.833
'He learnt how to lie...'

02:24:04.166 --> 02:24:07.958
'and taught us how to love.'

02:24:09.208 --> 02:24:12.125
'He loved me enough,
to let me go.'

02:24:12.916 --> 02:24:18.291
He came here naked,
as children do.

02:24:19.458 --> 02:24:25.249
Asked a lot of questions,
as children do.

02:24:27.416 --> 02:24:30.541
And then one day...

02:24:31.958 --> 02:24:33.749
he went away.

02:24:35.833 --> 02:24:39.000
Four billion miles away.

02:24:41.666 --> 02:24:44.458
He left me two parting gifts.

02:24:47.666 --> 02:24:49.958
Sarfaraz...

02:24:50.750 --> 02:24:52.125
and Papa.

02:24:55.916 --> 02:24:57.374
Till the time I am alive,

02:24:58.083 --> 02:25:02.583
I'll look at his planet every night
and wave.

02:25:05.083 --> 02:25:08.541
I'm sure, he'll do the same.

02:25:12.791 --> 02:25:14.666
I miss him.

02:25:54.500 --> 02:25:58.791
'Fellow astronauts,
prepare to land on Earth.'

02:25:58.916 --> 02:26:02.999
'Remember the four
Earth Survival Commandments.'

02:26:03.125 --> 02:26:06.124
'One, do not roam around naked.'

02:26:06.208 --> 02:26:11.708
'Cuddling, making love, etcetera,
must be done in closed rooms.'

02:26:11.916 --> 02:26:15.958
'But fighting and making war
is allowed in the open.'

02:26:16.250 --> 02:26:20.000
'Two, beware of the language,
it's confusing.'

02:26:20.083 --> 02:26:23.791
'If Earthlings say,
"I love chicken and fish."

02:26:23.875 --> 02:26:27.583
'It doesn't mean that they love animals,'

02:26:27.666 --> 02:26:32.208
'but that those animals are
on the lunch menu.'

02:26:32.458 --> 02:26:37.458
'The gap between the thought and
the speech is our topic of research.'

02:26:37.833 --> 02:26:41.500
'Three, on landing,
find dancing cars for clothes.'

02:26:41.583 --> 02:26:44.708
'Hide your remotes
deep in your underwear,'

02:26:44.875 --> 02:26:48.958
'safe from thieves.'

02:26:49.041 --> 02:26:52.291
'And four, the mother commandment.'

02:26:52.375 --> 02:26:56.708
'If anyone says,
"I'll connect you to God."

02:26:56.791 --> 02:27:01.208
'Dump the research, take a U-turn
and run for your life.'

02:27:13.875 --> 02:27:16.375
Come, don't be afraid.

02:27:21.875 --> 02:27:23.791
What are you goggling at?

02:27:25.458 --> 02:27:28.083
I have a question.
- What?

02:27:29.125 --> 02:27:33.250
On your last visit,
how often were you whacked?

02:27:41.750 --> 02:27:44.208
What's this?
- Self-defense!

02:27:45.083 --> 02:27:47.166
Oh, I see.
Safety gadgets?

02:27:47.333 --> 02:27:50.625
Let's go.
- Not there! This way.

02:27:50.708 --> 02:27:52.000
Kaput!
